The Integrity Group Against Corruption has raised an alarm alleging that it has uncovered plots by some persons to unseat the Attorney-General of the Federation (AGF) and minister of justice, Abubakar Malami, SAN. According to the group it has uncovered an email from one Olaruwanju Suraju who claimed to be the chairman of one Civil Society Against Corruption, which indicates a desperate move to cast aspersions against Malami. Chairman of the group, Bello Gambo Iliya made the allegation on Tuesday, July 28 while speaking to journalists. According to him, the email dated Monday, July 27 was intended to garner support from civil society organisations against Malami. He said the writer email was intended to garner support from civil society organisations support to pitch President Muhammadu Buhari against his appointee. Malami. “It was clearly verified that the said man was busy struggling to get support from civil society organisations against the Attorney General of the Federation and minister of justice,” he stated. Illiya, however, appealed to Malami to remain resolute in the fight against corruption, adding that “people like Lanre are survivalists trying to revive themselves through sponsorship against authorities fighting corruption in the country.”